  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The rationale of this research is to determine if patients with lupus and presenting retinal
      &quot;pseudo-drusen-like&quot; deposits have genetic and complement-related similarities with AMD
      patients.

      Based on the results obtained, this study could lead to future research that could better
      target the treatment of patients with lupus or patients with AMD (Age related Macular
      Degeneration).

      The primary objective is to check if patients with lupus, treated or not with antimalarial
      drugs, with &quot;pseudo-drusen-like&quot; deposits have a different complement profile (functional
      exploration of complement, complement factors, genetic complement polymorphisms involved in
      AMD) compared to patients without &quot;pseudo-drusen-like&quot; deposits.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
